TY  - JOUR
T1  - Team Member Change, Flux in Coordination, and Performance: Effects of Strategic Core Roles, Information Transfer, and Cognitive Ability
AU  - Summers, James K.
AU  - Humphrey, Stephen E.
AU  - Ferris, Gerald R.
Y1  - 2012/04/01
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2010.0175
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2010.0175
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 314
EP  - 338
VL  - 55
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We developed and tested the conditions under which team member change results in flux in team coordination and consequently affects team performance. Results showed that team member change caused high levels of flux in coordination when a member changed to a more strategically core role, or there was low information transfer during the change. Furthermore, coupling strategic ?core role holder? change with the relative cognitive ability of a new member was associated with even greater levels of flux in coordination.
AB  - We developed and tested the conditions under which team member change results in flux in team coordination and consequently affects team performance. Results showed that team member change caused high levels of flux in coordination when a member changed to a more strategically core role, or there was low information transfer during the change. Furthermore, coupling strategic ?core role holder? change with the relative cognitive ability of a new member was associated with even greater levels of flux in coordination.
